<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 11 at 9:59PM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN HASKELL...
NORTHWESTERN LATIMER AND SOUTHEASTERN PITTSBURG COUNTIES THROUGH 1030
PM CST...
At 959 PM CST, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Alderson, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Wilburton...
Hartshorne...                     Krebs...
Quinton...                        Alderson...
Higgins...                        Damon...
Robbers Cave State Park...        Haileyville...
Gowen...                          Panola...
Dow...                            Bache...
Featherston...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
